## Before you start

Read **[docs/template/TEMPLATE.md](./docs/template/TEMPLATE.md)** if this fork
deploys on Replit. It documents every friction point hit on the first fork
(pnpm version, Chromium libs, deploy image size, etc.) and how the template
already handles them. Skim the "Quick start (post-template-hardening)" section
at the bottom for the happy-path flow.

## Agent workflow (mstack plugin)

- [ ] Install the **mstack** agent workflow. It's a Claude Code plugin already
  declared in `.claude/settings.json` (`vbhadala/mstack`). When you open the
  repo and trust the folder, Claude Code prompts you to install `mstack@mstack`
  — accept it, or run `/plugin install mstack@mstack`. It provides the
  `/mstack:*` skills (plan → review → code, qa, debug, mockup, design-system,
  ux-audit, research, auto).

## Local dev sanity

- [ ] Run `pnpm setup` to generate `.env.local` (auth secret + `DATABASE_URL`),
  then `pnpm db:migrate`, then `pnpm doctor` to confirm config + database +
  migrations are green before you build or deploy.

## Required before first deploy

- [ ] Create Neon project + branch for `{{SLUG}}`.
- [ ] Create Postmark server + sender signature.
- [ ] Set up OAuth apps (Google, Apple, if used by the fork).
- [ ] Substitute the mobile universal-link values in one shot: **`pnpm setup-deeplinks`**.
  It prompts for Apple Team ID, iOS bundle, Android package, the **app-signing**
  SHA-256 (not the upload key), and the deep-link host, then rewrites
  `apps/mobile/app.config.ts` + `apps/web/public/.well-known/*` with validation.
  Prefer editing by hand? See [docs/fork-setup.md](./docs/fork-setup.md).
- [ ] `eas init` to bind this fork to a new EAS project.
- [ ] Configure **deploy** secrets — for a Replit deploy, add them in Replit
  Secrets (not `.env.local`). The shipped CI needs no secrets; add GitHub repo
  secrets only if you add a workflow that hits real services. Full map:
  [docs/fork-setup.md](./docs/fork-setup.md).
- [ ] `pnpm db:migrate` against the new Neon database.
- [ ] First-boot smoke: `pnpm dev`, sign up, verify email lands.
- [ ] Grant yourself admin: `pnpm make-admin you@example.com` (or `pnpm make-admin` to promote the first signup).

## Verify the rename worked

```
rm pnpm-lock.yaml && pnpm install
pnpm gen:mobile-tw
pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test
pnpm syncpack lint && pnpm dedupe --check
```

Bundle smoke (mobile):

```
pnpm --filter {{NAMESPACE}}/mobile exec expo export --platform ios --output-dir /tmp/expo-bundle
grep -rlE "@mlabs/|MLabs Template|mlabs-mobile|mlabs\.example\.com" . --exclude-dir=node_modules --exclude=pnpm-lock.yaml || true
```

Both should come back clean (the grep should print nothing).

